    	<div class="col-4 p-5 plummers text-white">
    		<h4 class="text-center">Why Are Engineers Called "Plummers"?</h4>
    		<hr>
    		<p>We believe that engineers are called plummers because of the deep rooted military past… Allow us to elaborate. Most engineering in the day was done by military engineers (cheap labour, right?). Now, have you ever wondered why they used Plum bobs and everything they built was ‘just plum.’ Well, this is because the general at the time, Gen. (and noted Professor) Plum invented said engineering instrument and damn did it work good. This is also why engineers are purple, the colour of the Plum.</p>
